    {
      "fieldname": "fcm_instructions_html",
      "fieldtype": "HTML",
      "label": "Setup Instructions",
      "options": "<div style=\"background: #e3f2fd; padding: 15px; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid #2196f3; margin: 10px 0;\">\n<h4 style=\"color: #1565c0; margin-top: 0;\">Firebase Cloud Messaging Setup Guide</h4>\n<ol style=\"color: #333; line-height: 2;\">\n<li>Go to <a href=\"https://console.firebase.google.com\" target=\"_blank\">Firebase Console</a></li>\n<li>Create a new project or select an existing one</li>\n<li>Go to <strong>Project Settings</strong> (gear icon)</li>\n<li>Select <strong>Service Accounts</strong> tab</li>\n<li>Click <strong>Generate New Private Key</strong></li>\n<li>Download the JSON file and copy its contents</li>\n<li>Paste the full JSON in the <strong>FCM Service Account JSON</strong> field above</li>\n<li>Copy the <strong>Project ID</strong> from the General tab</li>\n</ol>\n<hr style=\"border-color: #bbdefb;\">\n<div style=\"background: #fff3e0; padding: 10px; border-radius: 5px; margin-top: 10px;\">\n<p style=\"color: #e65100; margin: 0;\"><strong>Important Notes:</strong></p>\n<ul style=\"color: #333; margin: 5px 0;\">\n<li>Service Account JSON is the recommended method (FCM v1 API)</li>\n<li>Legacy Server Key is deprecated by Google</li>\n<li>Make sure to enable Cloud Messaging API in Google Cloud Console</li>\n<li>Add your Android app in Firebase to get <code>google-services.json</code></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>"
    },
